cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper deals with deep learning for medical image analysis, specifically for computed tomography (CT) data. The paper focuses on the development of a system to directly process raw CT data in sinogram-space, bypassing the intermediary step of image reconstruction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning algorithms for classification tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of sparsely sampled sinograms, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the potential clinical applications of the proposed system, which could also fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
